#Lab 02 - Windows-local-user-administration

## Objective
Create and manage local Windows user accounts while learning how Windows uses groups and permissions to control access.

## Environment 

- Oracle VirtualBox
- Windows 10 Pro
- 4 GB RAM
- 2 CPU CORES
- 60 GB Virtual Hard Disk

## Steps Performed
1. Opened Computer Management.
2. Navigated to Local Users and Groups.
3. Explored built-in local accounts.
4. Created a new local user named Alice Johnson.
5. Configured the account description and password.
6. Reviewed account properties.
7. Explored the General, Member Of, and Profile tabs.
8. Added Alice to the Administrators group.
9. Logged into Alice's account.
10. Compared administrator permissions with a standard user.

## Skills Practiced
- Computer Management
- Local user administration
- Windows group management
- Administrator vs Standard User permissions
- Windows account configuration

## Lessons Learned
- Windows places new accounts into the Users group by default.
- The Principle of Least Privilege reduces security risks.
- Groups simplify permission management.
- Administrator permissions are assigned through group membership.
- User Account Control (UAC) provides an additional security layer even for administrators.

## Outcome
Successfully created and managed local Windows user accounts while learning how Windows permissions and security groups work.
